      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "&quot;<i>writing charset like this &quot;UTF-8&quot; (uppercase)</i>&quot; - makes no difference, as media type parameters are case-insensitive; &quot;<i>instead of putting &quot;;&quot; after text/xml, just putting &quot;,&quot; (comma)</i>&quot; - is syntaxically wrong. A media type is separated from its parameters by a semicolon only, and the parameters are separated from each other by semicolons, too."
